# Render .NET Deploy

Source: Render deploy logs + `docs/04_RUNTIME_FRAMEWORKS_AND_PACKAGES.md`

## Docker images (.NET 10 only)

| Service | Build image | Runtime image | Port / entry |
|---------|-------------|---------------|--------------|
| API | `mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:10.0` | `mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:10.0` | `ASPNETCORE_URLS=http://+:8080`, `EXPOSE 8080`, health at `/health/ready` |
| Worker | `sdk:10.0` | `aspnet:10.0` | No port; `ENTRYPOINT ["dotnet", "Product.Worker.dll"]` |

Workers **must** use `aspnet:10.0`, not `runtime:10.0`. Suite workers reference `STLCompliance.Shared`, which pulls in `Microsoft.AspNetCore.App`. Using `runtime:10.0` builds succeed but startup fails with:

```
Framework: 'Microsoft.AspNetCore.App', version '10.0.0' (x64)
No frameworks were found.
```

```dockerfile
# ❌ BAD — worker runtime missing ASP.NET Core shared framework
FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/runtime:10.0 AS runtime

# ✅ GOOD — aspnet image includes Microsoft.AspNetCore.App
FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:10.0 AS runtime
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app/publish .
ENTRYPOINT ["dotnet", "Shared.Worker.dll"]
```

## Publish settings

- Always publish from repo root context: `dockerContext: .` in `render.yaml`
- Use `/p:UseAppHost=false` (Linux container has no apphost exe)
- Do not pin different .NET major versions across products
- Do not commit `bin/` or `obj/` artifacts

```dockerfile
RUN dotnet publish path/to/Project.csproj -c Release -o /app/publish /p:UseAppHost=false
```

## Common Render failures

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Build: project not found | Wrong `dockerContext` or path in Dockerfile | Keep `dockerContext: .`; use paths like `apps/nexarr-api/NexArr.Api/NexArr.Api.csproj` |
| Runtime: `Microsoft.AspNetCore.App` missing | Worker on `runtime:10.0` | Switch worker runtime stage to `aspnet:10.0` |
| Health check timeout | API not on 8080 or no `/health/ready` | Set `ASPNETCORE_URLS=http://+:8080`; map health checks in shared hosting |
| Restore errors in Docker | Missing copied files | `COPY . .` from repo root before `dotnet restore`/`publish` |

## Pre-push checklist

Before pushing changes that touch APIs, workers, Dockerfiles, or shared .NET packages:

1. `dotnet build STLCompliance.slnx -c Release`
2. `dotnet test STLCompliance.slnx -c Release --no-build` (or build + test)
3. If Dockerfiles changed, confirm runtime image matches service type (API and worker → `aspnet:10.0`)
4. Do not stage `bin/`, `obj/`, or local publish output
